│ This occurred for a bundle of GEPs whose index instructions (zext/sext) originated in a predecessor basic block.                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Root Cause:                                                                                                                                                                              │
│ Strict debug assertions in getLastInstructionInBundle required all scalar instructions in a bundle (except specific exempt cases) to be in the same basic block, disallowing safe,       │
│ speculatively executable predecessor-block index instructions used by GEPs.                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Resolution:                                                                                                                                                                              │
│ In llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp:                                                                                                                                      │
