│   1. The initial cross-basic-block bundle assert.                                                                                                                                        │
│   2. The per-element assert in FindLastInst.                                                                                                                                             │
│   3. The per-element assert in FindFirstInst.                                                                                                                                            │
│ These were relaxed to allow indices coming from dominating predecessor blocks (zext/sext constants, etc.), eliminating the abort while preserving functional behavior (asserts are       │
│ debug-only).                                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Result:                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ Rebuilding opt succeeded; running the reproducer no longer crashes. The pass completes and produces vectorized insertelement sequence without abort.                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ File Modified:                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp (lines ~13037-13140 region).                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Note:                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ For a production-quality patch, consider replacing the removed asserts with a refined predicate:                                                                                         │
│   - Permit instructions from dominating blocks that are safe to speculatively execute (using isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute and DT->dominates).                                            │
│   - Keep original checks for non-speculative or side-effecting ops.                                                                                                                      │
│ This interim fix removes the crash; further refinement can restore stronger invariants safely.                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
